eapli.ecafeteria.domain.authz

Class SystemUser

  • java.lang.Object
    • eapli.ecafeteria.domain.authz.SystemUser
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    eapli.framework.domain.ddd.AggregateRoot<Username>, eapli.framework.domain.ddd.DomainEntity<Username>, eapli.framework.domain.Identifiable<Username>, eapli.framework.dto.DTOable, eapli.framework.visitor.Visitable<eapli.framework.dto.GenericDTO>, Serializable

    @Entity
public class SystemUser
extends Object
implements eapli.framework.domain.ddd.AggregateRoot<Username>, eapli.framework.dto.DTOable, eapli.framework.visitor.Visitable<eapli.framework.dto.GenericDTO>, Serializable
    An application user. This class represents application users. It follows a DDD approach where User is the root entity of the User Aggregate and all of its properties are instances of value objects. This approach may seem a little more complex than just having String or native type attributes but provides for real semantic of the domain and follows the Single Responsibility Pattern
    Author:
    Paulo Gandra Sousa
